					</div>
				<h1 itemprop="headline" class="entry-title">Today in Small Business: The Bacon Bowl</h1>
		<div class="story-meta-footer">
			<address class="byline author vcard" itemprop="author creator" itemtype="//schema.org/Person">
				By Gene Marks			</address>
			<!-- date published --><time class="dateline " datetime="2014-09-19T15:01:27+00:00" itemprop="datePublished">September 19, 2014 11:01 am</time>
			<!-- date updated --><span class="visually-hidden updated">September 19, 2014 11:01 am</span><button class="button comments-button  theme-kicker" data-skip-to-para-id="">
</button>
		</div>
			</header>
		<div class="entry-content"><div id="sharetools-story" class="sharetools theme-classic sharetools-story" data-shares="email|Email,facebook|Share,twitter|Tweet,save|Save,show-all|More,ad" data-url="//boss.blogs.nytimes.com/2014/09/19/today-in-small-business-the-bacon-bowl/" data-title="Today in Small Business: The Bacon Bowl" data-description="How Alibaba shared the wealth with employees. Rewarding customers for writing negative Yelp reviews. And why it&#039;s definitely time to take a break!">
				<div class="ad sharetools-inline-article-ad"></div>
				<div id="MiddleLeft" class="ad middle-left-ad nocontent robots-nocontent"></div>
				</div><div class="inlineModule"><div class="entry"><h6 class="kicker"><a href="//boss.blogs.nytimes.com/category/dashboard/">Dashboard</a></h6><p class="summary">A daily roundup of small-business developments.</p></div></div>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">Whatâs affecting me, my clients and other small-business owners today.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>The Economy</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Travelers in the United States are <a href="//blogs.wsj.com/economics/2014/09/18/travelers-and-airfare-spending-take-flight-with-improving-economy/?">spending more on flights</a>.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Employees</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Fewer than half of Americans <a href="//www.usatoday.com/story/news/nation/2014/09/18/flu-shot-recommendations/15824917/">get a flu shot</a>.</li>
<li>Research shows that the secret to working productively is <a href="//www.fastcompany.com/3035605/how-to-be-a-success-at-everything/the-exact-amount-of-time-you-should-work-every-day">taking frequent breaks</a>.</li>
<li>How Alibaba shared the wealth, minting <a href="//dealbook.nytimes.com/2014/09/18/alibaba-with-its-i-p-o-mints-millionaires-and-risk-takers/">thousands of Internet millionaires</a>.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Manufacturing</strong></p>
<ul>
<ul>
<li>Here&#8217;s how robots are working their way <a href="//online.wsj.com/articles/robots-work-their-way-into-small-factories-1410979100">into small factories</a>.</li>
<li>How a plant manufacturing the <a href="//online.wsj.com/articles/how-the-bacon-bowl-gave-hope-to-a-tiny-townthen-left-for-china-1410982645">Perfect Bacon Bowl</a> gave hope to but ultimately disappointed a tiny town in Mississippi.</li>
</ul>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><span id="more-88741"></span></p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Management</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Larry Ellison <a href="//www.reuters.com/article/2014/09/18/us-oracle-ceo-idUSKBN0HD2HP20140918?fee">steps aside</a> as Oracleâs chief executive.</li>
<li>The maker of a popular snack mix <a href="//upstart.bizjournals.com/companies/startups/2014/09/17/a-snack-mix-entrepreneurs-dilemma-customers-cant.html">needs capital</a> to solve a good problem: His customers want more of his mix.</li>
<li>A small-business lawyer <a href="//www.smallbizdaily.com/17892/happy-50th-birthday-score-2/">praises Score</a> on its 50th birthday.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Marketing</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>A lawyer faces <a href="//www.fastcompany.com/3035920/fast-feed/california-lawyer-faces-suspension-for-fake-photoshops-with-dozens-of-celebrities">suspension for</a> allegedly faking photos taken with dozens of celebrities.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Exporting</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Immigrant-owned small businesses have a tremendous advantage when <a href="//money.cnn.com/2014/09/18/smallbusiness/immigrant-entrepreneurs-exports/index.html?s">exporting to their home countries</a>.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Social Media</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Here&#8217;s a new <a href="//venturebeat.com/2014/09/18/small-businesses-have-their-own-social-network-today-in-brazzlebox/">online community</a> for small and home-based businesses.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Finance</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>A well-known retailer of fishing, hunting and other outdoor-recreation gear <a href="//online.wsj.com/articles/bass-pro-shops-considers-financing-alternatives-1411058952?mod=pls_whats_news_us_business_f">is considering</a> alternatives for raising money.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Retail</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Starbucks <a href="//www.usatoday.com/story/money/business/2014/09/16/starbucks-frappuccino-fast-food-restaurants/15727699/">tests</a> a Frappuccino Mini.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Entrepreneurship<br />
</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Dell <a href="//www.dell.com/learn/us/en/uscorp1/press-releases/2014-09-16-dell-founders-club-50-fall-class">announces</a> a new class of 50 start-ups to watch.</li>
<li>For nearly 30 years, an entrepreneurial farmer has <a href="//www.bbc.com/news/business-29082091">devoted himself</a> to setting up the first commercial wasabi farm in North America.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Around the Country</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>The &#8220;Uber effect&#8221; has reduced San Francisco&#8217;s <a href="//www.engadget.com/2014/09/17/SF-taxi-decline/">use of cabs</a> 65 percent.</li>
<li>A writer in Missouri <a href="//www.nwmissourinews.com/features/article_de4447f6-3ec5-11e4-9c96-0017a43b2370.html">takes a tour</a> of the local stores on his townâs Main Street.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Around the World</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Panama <a href="//www.mnn.com/health/fitness-well-being/stories/the-worlds-happiest-country-in-2013-was?">may be</a> the happiest country in the world.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Online</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>A restaurant in California is <a href="https://www.americanexpress.com/us/small-business/openforum/articles/why-one-business-is-begging-for-terrible-yelp-reviews/">rewarding customers</a> who give it terrible reviews on Yelp.</li>
<li>Amazon <a href="//www.entrepreneur.com/article/237613">scoops up</a> the â.buyâ domain for $4.6 million.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Ideas</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>A new traffic radar gun <a href="https://www.yahoo.com/tech/new-traffic-radar-gun-will-detect-when-drivers-are-97820764259.html?src=rss">will detect</a> when drivers are texting.</li>
<li>A new application will allow property managers to <a href="//thenextweb.com/apps/2014/09/18/remotely-launches-home-automation-service-property-managers/">manage rental properties</a> remotely.</li>
<li>A mobile app <a href="//www.crainsnewyork.com/article/20140918/TECHNOLOGY/140919872/brooklyn-tech-company-rates-your-food">that can tell users</a> how some 100,000 products rate for sustainability, social impact, environmental friendliness and healthfulness.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Technology</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><a href="//www.fastcompany.com/3035947/fast-feed/microsoft-cuts-another-2100-jobs?p">Microsoft</a> and <a href="//www.zdnet.com/toshiba-cuts-900-jobs-amid-pc-business-restructuring-7000033820/">Toshiba</a> cut jobs.</li>
<li>College students <a href="//www.itworld.com/career/436261/college-students-learning-cobol-make-more-money">who learn Cobol</a> as part of their college studies are being hired at a higher starting salary than their peers.</li>
<li>Elon Musk predicts that <a href="//gizmodo.com/elon-musk-self-driving-teslas-are-just-six-years-away-1636534369">self-driving Teslas</a> are just six years away.</li>
<li>Home Depotâs credit card hack <a href="//mashable.com/2014/09/18/home-depot-hack-could-be-largest-ever-56-million-credit-cards-at-risk/?">could be</a> the largest ever.</li>
</ul>
